---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Callout from '../components/Callout.astro';
---

<Layout title="About Our Team" description="TerraSearch Geophsyical, LLC's team of dedicated archeologists are led by Dr. David Leslie and Mr. David George. Together they have half a century of experience in the field. Learn more about them on this page.   ">
	<main>
        <div id="hero">
            <h1 id="Hero--text">
                Led by <span>David Leslie</span> & <span>David George</span>, our team is composed of highly regarded experts in the fields of geoarcheology and historic preservation.
            </h1>
        </div>
        <div id="people">
            <div class="creds">
                <div class="creds--title">
                    <h2>David Leslie, PhD, RPA</h2>
                    <div class="bar"></div>
                </div>
                <ul>
                    <li>Bachelor of Arts in Sociology and Anthropology, Minor in Geography, West Virginia University, 2006</li>
                    <li>Master of Arts in Anthropology, Florida Atlantic University, 2008</li>
                    <li>Doctoral Degree in Anthropology, University of Connecticut, 2016</li>
                    <li>Registered Professional Archaeologist</li>
                </ul>         
            </div>
            <img src="/davel.webp" height="600" width="900" alt="Picture of David Leslie"/>
            <div class="bio">
                <p>Dr. Leslie has over 15 years of geoarchaeological experience, completing over one hundred investigations under all phases of Section 106 work throughout the greater Northeast.  He is also the Director of Archaeological Research at Heritage Consultants, as well as a Research Scientist in the Department of Anthropology at the University of Connecticut and the President of the Archaeological Society of Connecticut.  Dr. Leslie is also actively participates on various boards of regional archaeological societies, including the Conference on New England Archaeology and Eastern State Archaeological Federation, and serves on the Editorial Board of the journal Northeast Anthropology. </p>
            </div>
            <div class="creds">
                <div class="creds--title">
                    <h2>David George, MA, RPA</h2>
                    <div class="bar"></div>
                 </div>
                <ul>
                    <li>Bachelor of Science in Business Management, Ithaca College, 1990</li>
                    <li>Master of Arts in Anthropology, University of Connecticut, 1992</li>
                    <li>Introduction to Federal Projects and Historic Preservation Law, Section 106 Compliance, 1999</li>
                    <li>Federal Energy Regulatory Commission, Environmental Report Preparation Seminar, 2003</li>
                    <li>Registered Professional Archaeologist</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
            <img id="george--img" src="/daveg.webp" height="600" width="900" alt="Picture of David George"/>
            <div class="bio"> 
                <p>
                    Mr. George has over 30 years of archaeological experience, completing hundreds of investigations under all phases of Section 106 work throughout the United States.  He is also the President and owner of Heritage Consultants, and brings a wealth of cultural resource management knowledge and experience to bear on all of TerraSearch's work.   
                 </p>
            </div> 
        </div>
    </main>
</Layout>

<style>
    #hero {
        padding: 140px 80px 80px 80px;
        background-image: url("/bg-topo.webp");
        height: fit-content;
        background-position: center;
        background-repeat: no-repeat;
        background-size: cover;
        position: relative;
        display: flex;
        align-items: center;
        justify-content: center;
    }

    #Hero--text {
        background-color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.9);
        height: 100%;
        font-size: 48px;
        line-height: 70px;
        letter-spacing: -0.015em;
        color: #375B2B;
        padding:80px 64px;
    }

    #Hero--text > span {
        text-decoration: underline;
        text-decoration-color: rgba(254,127,45,1);
    }

    #people {
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
        grid-auto-flow: row dense;
        position: relative;
        height: fit-content;
    }
    .creds {
        padding:72px 80px;
    }

    .creds--title {
        width:fit-content;
        margin-bottom: 16px;
    }
    .creds--title h2 {
        font-weight: 300;
        font-size: 48px;
        line-height: 36px;
        letter-spacing: -0.015em;
        color: #375B2B;
        margin-bottom:10px;
    }

    .creds--title .bar{
        height: 2px;
        width: 100%;
        margin: 2px auto 0 auto;
        background-color: #375B2B;
    }

    .creds > ul {
        list-style-type: none;
        padding:24px 0px 0 0px;
    }

    .creds  ul  li {
        margin-bottom:24px;
    }

    .bio {
        grid-column: span 2;
        background-color: #28421F;
        color: #fff;
        padding:64px 80px;
    }

    .bio > p {
        font-family: 'Montserrat';
        font-style: normal;
        font-weight: 400;
        font-size: 18px;
        font-size: 18px;
        line-height: 30px;
        letter-spacing: -0.015em;
        margin-bottom:24px;
    }

    #people > img {
        max-width: 100%;
        max-height: 530px;
        width:100%;
        object-fit: cover;
        background-size: cover;
        background-color: #d6cbb9;
    }
    #george--img{
        grid-column: 1 / 2;
        grid-row: 3 / 4;
    }

    @media only screen and (max-width: 999px) { 
        #hero {
            padding: 92px 16px 32px 16px;
        }

        #Hero--text {
            font-size: 32px;
            padding:24px;
            line-height: 48px;
        }

        #people {
            grid-template-columns: 1fr;
        }

        #george--img{
            grid-column: unset;
            grid-row: unset;
        }

        .creds{
            padding:32px;
        }
        .creds--title > h2 {
            line-height: 48px;
        }

        #people > .img { 
            width: 100%;
            aspect-ratio: 1 / 1;
        }

        .bio {
            grid-column: span 1;
            padding: 24px;
        }

    }

</style>